-- Hercules preliminary Q1 earnings, revenue rise
-- 
-- Thu Apr 19, 2007 6:32am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/04/19/us-hercules-results-idUSWNAS678320070419

 

 (Reuters) - Hercules Inc. HPC.N posted higher quarterly earnings, and its net sales increased 9.6 percent, excluding the impact of the FiberVisions transaction. 

 For the first quarter, the company earned 64 cents per share on revenue of $502.3 million, compared with 13 cents per share in the year ago period, the chemicals maker said in its preliminary results statement. The latest quarter earnings included 41 cents per share from the resolution of IRS audit issues for the years 1993 through 2003, it said. (Reporting by Shailesh Kuber in Bangalore)